message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Italy in the past 100 years is the end of World War II and the subsequent downfall of Benito Mussolini's fascist regime. Italy was one of the Axis powers during the war, and after years of conflict and occupation, the country faced a period of political and social upheaval. In April 1945, Mussolini was captured and executed by Italian partisans, marking the end of his dictatorship. This event led to the establishment of a democratic republic in Italy and set the stage for the country's post-war reconstruction and economic development.
